Pre-Game Insights: Namibia and Oman face off in the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2024 at Kensington Oval, Barbados.
Namibia has dominated with four wins out of six matches against Oman.
Kensington Oval pitch offers an ideal balance for both batsmen and bowlers, particularly favouring fast bowlers.
The T20I record at Kensington Oval reflects the pitch's favourability for the team batting first, with 16 wins compared to 7 for the team bowling first.
Selecting top-order batsmen and quality all-rounders could prove to be beneficial for fantasy cricket enthusiasts for this match.
Key players for Namibia include Gerhard Erasmus and David Wiese, while Aqib Ilyas Sulheri is a key player for Oman.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kensington Oval has a seating capacity of 28,000 and was established in 1871.
The highest total recorded at the ground is 224/5 by West Indies against England, while the lowest is 80/10 by Afghanistan against South Africa.
